import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
data=pd.read_csv("C:\\Users\\ASUS\\Downloads\\WEEK3 new\\WEEK3\\Immigration\\security check.csv")

count_positive = 0
count_negative = 0
count_neutral = 0

for sentiment in data['sentiment']:
    if sentiment == 'Positive':
        count_positive += 1
    else:
        count_negative += 1
total=len(data)
positive_response= (count_positive / total) * 100
negative_response = (count_negative / total) * 100
myexplode = [0.2, 0]
y=[positive_response,negative_response]
plt.pie(y,labels=[str(round(positive_response,2))+"%",str(round(negative_response,2))+"%"],explode = myexplode, shadow = True,colors=["g","r"])
plt.title("Check IN tweet % distribution")
plt.legend(["positive","negative"])
plt.show()

LDA for positive tweets¶

In [5]:
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer
from sklearn.decomposition import LatentDirichletAllocation

from sklearn.feature_extraction import text

# Read the positive reviews data
positive_reviews = pd.read_csv("C:\\Users\\ASUS\\Downloads\\WEEK3 new\\WEEK3\\Immigration\\security check - Copy.csv")

# Combine reviews into a list
reviews = positive_reviews['tweet'].tolist()

# Create a custom stop words list if needed
custom_stop_words = ["read", "good", "disney", "yorker", "day", "didn", "stay", "great", "check", "booked", "like", "die", "told", "friendly", "clean", "sehr", "das", "zimmer", "und", "nice", "did", "was", "really", "safe", "walk", "close", "got"]

# Extend the default English stop words list with custom stop words
stop_words = list(text.ENGLISH_STOP_WORDS) + custom_stop_words

# Vectorize the text data
vectorizer = CountVectorizer(max_df=0.95, min_df=2, stop_words=stop_words)
X = vectorizer.fit_transform(reviews)

# Apply LDA for topic modeling
num_topics = 5
lda = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=num_topics, random_state=42)
lda.fit(X)

# Extract top words for each topic
feature_names = vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()
topics = []
for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(lda.components_):
    top_words_idx = topic.argsort()[-10:]
    top_words = [feature_names[i] for i in top_words_idx]
    topics.append(top_words)

# Print the top words for each topic (possible reasons for positive reviews)
for i, topic in enumerate(topics):
    print(f"Topic {i + 1}: {', '.join(topic)}")

Topic 1: use, process, modi, reach, bag, help, traffic, delhi, flight, mumbai
Topic 2: hand, asked, took, let, use, today, things, modi, chennai, bag
Topic 3: today, use, traffic, process, flight, bottles, international, hand, frm, travelling
Topic 4: today, use, traffic, process, asked, bottles, reach, flight, pm, chennai
Topic 5: pm, traffic, bag, help, let, took, international, process, reached, flight

Observation on positive tweet¶

  • ### Immigration and security checks are an important part of keeping travelers safe and preventing crime.
  • ### Immigration and security officials are working hard to protect travelers and keep them safe.
  • ### Immigration and security checks are becoming increasingly efficient and streamlined, thanks to new technologies and procedures.

Recommendation¶

  • ### Continue to improve the efficiency and streamline of immigration and security checks.
  • ### Use new technologies to make immigration and security checks more effective and less intrusive.
  • ### Train immigration and security officials to be polite and respectful of travelers.

Word Cloud for positive tweets¶

In [6]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from wordcloud import WordCloud

# Create a word cloud object
wc = WordCloud(background_color="white", max_font_size=50)

# Check the type of the topics variable
if isinstance(topics, list):
    # Convert the topics variable to a list of strings
    topics = [" ".join(topic) for topic in topics]

# Generate the word cloud
wc.generate(" ".join(topics))

# Plot the word cloud
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
plt.imshow(wc)
plt.axis("off")
plt.title("Top Words in Positive Reviews")
plt.show()

LDA for Negative tweets¶

In [11]:
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer
from sklearn.decomposition import LatentDirichletAllocation

# Read the negative reviews data
negative_reviews = pd.read_csv("C:\\Users\\ASUS\\Downloads\\WEEK3 new\\WEEK3\\Immigration\\security check - Copy (2).csv")

# Combine reviews into a list
reviews = negative_reviews['tweet'].tolist()

# Create a custom stop words list if needed
custom_stop_words = ["read", "good", "disney", "yorker", "day", "didn", "stay", "great", "check", "booked", "like", "die", "told", "friendly", "clean", "sehr", "das", "zimmer", "und", "nice", "did", "was", "really", "safe", "walk", "close", "got"]

# Convert the custom stop words to a list
custom_stop_words = list(custom_stop_words)

# Vectorize the text data with limited vocabulary
vectorizer = CountVectorizer(max_df=1.0, min_df=1, stop_words=custom_stop_words)  # Adjusted values
X = vectorizer.fit_transform(reviews)

# Apply LDA for topic modeling
num_topics = 2  # Due to the small dataset
lda = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=num_topics, random_state=42)
lda.fit(X)

# Extract top words for each topic
feature_names = vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()
topics = []
for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(lda.components_):
    top_words_idx = topic.argsort()[-10:]
    top_words = [feature_names[i] for i in top_words_idx]
    topics.append(top_words)

# Print the top words for each topic
for i, topic in enumerate(topics):
    print(f"Topic {i + 1}: {', '.join(topic)}")

Topic 1: bomb, security, slow, fastag, pathetically, morning, mess, accumulated, bangalore, airport
Topic 2: everyone, delayed, sarcastically, threat, whole, airport, bangalore, bomb, guards, security

Observation on negative tweet¶

  • ### Security at the Bangalore airport is inadequate, leading to delays, confusion, and inconvenience for passengers.
  • ### Security checks are slow and inefficient.
  • ### There is a lack of communication and coordination between security guards and other staff.
  • ### Passengers are being inconvenienced by long queues, delays, and confusion.

Recommendations:¶

  • ### The Bangalore airport authorities should conduct a comprehensive review of their security procedures and implement measures to improve the overall security and efficiency of the airport.
  • ### The airport authorities should increase the number of security staff, use faster technologies, and streamline the security process.
  • ### The airport authorities should improve communication and coordination between security guards and other staff.
  • ### The airport authorities should implement a system for passengers to report security concerns or incidents in a timely and confidential manner.
